  "text": "where x m and x s are positions of the master and slave, respectively. F m and F s denote the operational force and reaction force from the environment, respectively. Equations (1) and [CITATION_1] show that both the position and the force of the bilateral control system should be controlled simultaneously. However, it is impossible to realize position and force control simultaneously in one axis because of their opposite control stiffness. Therefore, (1) and (2) are transformed into dimensions of acceleration as shown in (3) and (4), respectively.",
